Senior administration officials from the United States and European Commission counterparts met to discuss progress and next steps towards achieving the U.S.-EU Agenda for Beating the Global Pandemic. They emphasized the importance of the transatlantic partnership and leadership in defeating the pandemic, strengthening the supply chain, and enhancing global health security. The meeting included a briefing on the Omicron variant and discussions on various topics such as vaccine donations, accelerating vaccinations, boosting global production of vaccines and supplies, and collaborating on health threat assessments and research and development. The delegations called for stronger actions and commitments from nations worldwide. They also highlighted the need for bold action to prepare for future health emergencies and pandemics, including the establishment of a Financial Intermediary Fund for global health security and pandemic preparedness in early 2022. The United States and the European Union will collaborate with various organizations to achieve this goal.